  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "單純曝光效應 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-mere-exposure-effect",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / familiarity / preference / trust</p>\n    <h1>單純曝光效應</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">Mere Exposure Effect</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">很多東西不是因為本身更好才被喜歡，而是因為它比較常被看見、比較熟，於是大腦對它比較放鬆。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要把『它真的更好』和『只是我比較熟所以比較不排斥』拆開，因為熟悉感常默默在替偏好加分。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>偏好心理 / 熟悉增益</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>Repeated exposure can increase liking or comfort</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>曝光頻率、熟悉感、辨識負擔、信任增益</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能看懂熟悉感如何影響使用者偏好、團隊選擇與個人評價</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>常見</span>\n      <span>熟悉</span>\n      <span>偏好</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>常看到的東西，常不知不覺就變得比較可接受</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">單純曝光效應提醒你：偏好有時不只是品質判斷，也有熟悉帶來的放鬆感。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>熟悉能降低認知負擔與不安，但若把熟悉誤當成品質，就可能錯把慣性當優越。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先辨認熟悉紅利</strong>\n        <p>偏好形成時，先問自己是不是只是比較常接觸。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再區分舒適與品質</strong>\n        <p>比較順眼不代表比較對，也不代表更適合。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後善用但別濫用</strong>\n        <p>設計上可以利用熟悉感降低摩擦，但不該拿它替真正價值補洞。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從一個大家越看越順眼、卻未必真的越好的方案開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">單純曝光效應在 UI、品牌、用字、團隊工具與人際印象裡都很常出現。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>團隊越看熟的 dashboard 越覺得合理，即使它其實藏了不少資訊結構問題；新方案雖更清楚，第一眼卻覺得怪。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>熟悉會讓人感到安全，於是偏好很容易在你還沒做完整比較前就先形成。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">反覆接觸同一刺激</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">熟悉感上升、戒心下降</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">偏好與信任被默默推高</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>單純曝光效應最有用的提醒是：舒服和優秀常不是同一件事。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看熟悉增益的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">如果某個選項老讓人說『看起來比較順』，很值得問那份順到底從哪來。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>接觸頻率</strong>\n        <p>你比較常看到、用到或聽到哪一個版本？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>初始摩擦</strong>\n        <p>新選項的不適，是品質差，還是只是尚未熟悉？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>信任遷移</strong>\n        <p>熟悉感是否被誤讀成可靠度與專業感？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>品牌與團隊慣性</strong>\n        <p>共同反覆暴露是否正在讓某些選項自帶優勢？</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>情境</th>\n            <th>熟悉帶來什麼</th>\n            <th>可能誤判什麼</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>UI 介面</td>\n            <td>看起來比較順手</td>\n            <td>把慣用版面當成最佳版面</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>品牌與名稱</td>\n            <td>比較信任</td>\n            <td>把曝光量當成品質訊號</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>內部工具</td>\n            <td>大家都習慣</td>\n            <td>忽略更合適方案需要的學習窗口</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼熟悉會讓人比較放鬆</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為大腦面對可預期刺激時，處理成本較低，也就更容易把它感成安全或可接受。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>處理流暢會誤導評價</strong>\n        <p>越容易處理的東西，越容易被感覺成比較好。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>陌生感像小風險</strong>\n        <p>即使沒明確壞處，陌生也常被體驗成輕微威脅。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>重複會慢慢洗掉戒心</strong>\n        <p>只要沒明顯負面事件，曝光本身就能提高接受度。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">單純曝光效應不是說熟悉一定誤導，而是提醒熟悉本身就在投票。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把熟悉感放回設計與選型判斷</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">對產品與工程團隊來說，很多『這個比較順』的評論，背後其實混著熟悉紅利。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>介面改版</strong>\n        <p>使用者剛開始的不適不一定代表設計更差，也可能只是曝光量還不夠。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>工具選型</strong>\n        <p>團隊熟悉某套工具後，會更容易高估它、低估新工具。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>文案與命名</strong>\n        <p>反覆曝光會提升接受度，因此第一次可讀性和長期熟悉效果要一起看。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>做設計比較時，別把『我比較熟』誤當成『它真的更好』。</li>\n      <li>若要推新方案，可以先增加低風險曝光，讓抗拒別只來自陌生感。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>三個常見誤讀</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">單純曝光效應不是說重複洗版就一定有效，而是說熟悉本來就在塑形偏好。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只要多看就會愛上</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>若刺激本身帶強烈負面經驗，曝光不一定能救。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>熟悉就等於好用</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>熟悉只降低負擔，不保證功能與結構更好。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>這只跟行銷有關</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>產品、團隊工具、文件與人際判斷都常見。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>我喜歡它，是因為它比較好，還是因為它比較熟</h2>\n      </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>若把兩個選項的曝光歷史重置，我還會給同樣評價嗎</strong>\n        <p>這能幫你檢查熟悉紅利的大小。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>新方案現在讓人不舒服，是品質問題還是只是陌生問題</strong>\n        <p>兩者對應的處理完全不同。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可接 processing fluency、branding 與 UI habituation。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 mere exposure effect 為主，再把概念帶回設計、品牌與工具偏好。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>Mere exposure effect 條目整理了重複接觸如何提高好感或接受度。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mere-exposure_effect\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Mere Exposure Effect</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>相鄰概念</strong>\n        <p>Processing fluency 可作為對照，理解容易處理為何會提升好感。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Processing_fluency\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Processing Fluency</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>設計背景</strong>\n        <p>Habituation 的一般討論有助於理解熟悉感如何改變體驗反應。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habituation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Habituation</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後可以挑一個你近期偏愛的工具，問自己：如果今天第一次看到它，我還會這麼快偏好嗎？</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
}
